X_i=\beta X_{i-1}+\varepsilon_i
i=1,2,...
\varepsilon_i
\mu
\sigma^2
0<\beta<1
X_0=0
X_i=\sum_{j=1}^i \varepsilon_j \beta ^{i-j}
E(X_i)=\mu((\beta^i-1)/(\beta-1))
X_i
E(X_i^2)
Var(X_i)=E(X_i^2)-[E(X_i)]^2
X_i
 X_i=\sum_{j=1}^i\beta^{i-j}\varepsilon_j\implies\mathrm{var}(X_i)=\sum_{j=1}^i\beta^{2(i-j)}\mathrm{var}(\varepsilon_j)=\sigma^2\sum_{j=1}^i\beta^{2(i-j)}=\sigma^2\frac{1-\beta^{2i}}{1-\beta^2}.
